Brazilian Stock Movers: B2W, MPX Energia, Vale Rise; Tim Tumbles

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-09-13T20:28:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/brazilian-stock-movers-b2w-mpx-energia-vale-rise-tim-tumbles.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index slid 0.3 percent to 55,543.97.  B2W Cia. Global do Varejo (BTOW3 BS) jumped 9.6 percent to
17.72 reais.  Brazil ’s largest online retailer rose on
speculation it may sell debt following parent company Lojas
Americanas SA’s decision to issue as much as 500 million reais
($292 million) of local bonds.  MPX Energia SA (MPXE3)  (MPXE3 BS) increased 0.9 percent to 38.30
reais. The energy company controlled by billionaire Eike Batista
said it finished talks to supply 200 megawatts of electricity
over 15 years to MMX Mineracao & Metalicos SA (MMXM3 BS),
Batista’s mining company. The contract is valued at 3.3 billion
reais, the companies said yesterday in a joint statement filed
to regulators.  Tim Participacoes SA (TCSL4)  (TIMP3 BS) fell 1.8 percent to 8.91
reais. Brazil’s second-largest wireless carrier may file a
request to sell new shares in Brazil as soon as this week,  Valor
Economico  reported, without saying how it obtained the
information. The company may raise 1 billion reais to 1.5
billion reais to pay for the takeover of AES Atimus Group in
July, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper said.  Vale SA (VALE3)  (VALE5 BS) advanced 0.7 percent to 41.56 reais. The
world’s largest iron-ore producer followed metal prices higher.
Copper rose for the first time in three sessions as a Peru
miners’ union planned a strike and French banks dismissed
concerns over their access to funds, easing speculation that
 Europe ’s sovereign-debt crisis will worsen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
